295
00:13:27,206 --> 00:13:28,572
[Coughs]

296
00:13:40,219 --> 00:13:42,139
- What's happened to you?
- It's my wisdom tooth.

297
00:13:42,188 --> 00:13:44,623
It's been throbbing all night,
and now it's started bleeding.

298
00:13:44,691 --> 00:13:46,557
All right, let's have a look.
Come on, open up.

299
00:13:46,626 --> 00:13:48,356
Which one?

300
00:13:48,428 --> 00:13:49,805
All right, Howard,
we'll get it fixed.

301
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,354
Go on, son.
Scarper.

302
00:13:52,598 --> 00:13:54,567
Now, look, if you're right,

303
00:13:54,634 --> 00:13:57,502
and you say your time
did not go on pause,

304
00:13:57,570 --> 00:14:00,301
and you say none of your
privileges were taken away,

305
00:14:00,373 --> 00:14:02,103
you should be entitled to them.

306
00:14:02,175 --> 00:14:03,108
Yeah.

307
00:14:03,176 --> 00:14:05,668
But they usually put them
at the end of your EDR.

308
00:14:05,745 --> 00:14:10,012
So if you got three months,
well, where did they put them?

309
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:11,608
Frigging push me!

310
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:14,813
I don't know.
Piss off.

311
00:14:14,887 --> 00:14:17,288
What you've got to do
is ask them to explain.

312
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:18,586
Ask the S.O.

313
00:14:18,658 --> 00:14:20,251
Mr. Morgan, can I have a word?

314
00:14:20,326 --> 00:14:22,693
Inside, Brian.
Go on.

315
00:14:22,762 --> 00:14:25,596
So, now you've met some of
the players, what do you think?

316
00:14:25,665 --> 00:14:27,293
Okay.
I think I can handle it.

317
00:14:27,367 --> 00:14:30,531
Mr. Morgan, there's something
going down... big.

318
00:14:30,603 --> 00:14:33,334
- I think it's a delivery.
- Bugger off, son.

319
00:14:34,474 --> 00:14:37,535
Welcome to Barfield.

320
00:14:45,218 --> 00:14:47,517
C Wing S.O.
has made a dental appointment

321
00:14:47,587 --> 00:14:50,352
for prisoner Howard Webster,
4:00 this afternoon.

322
00:14:50,423 --> 00:14:51,823
Anything you need.

323
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:55,391
Thought you were very good
this morning.

324
00:14:55,461 --> 00:14:57,225
I didn't.

325
00:14:57,296 --> 00:15:00,425
Oh, Mavis, um, was there any
kind of press release from HQ?

326
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:02,025
I'll check the fax machine.

327
00:15:02,101 --> 00:15:03,399
Everything okay?

328
00:15:03,469 --> 00:15:04,960
You missed your rounds
this morning.

329
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:07,871
Mr. Lyons isn't here, but I've
shown young Malahide the ropes.

330
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:09,151
Big of aggro going down, and...

331
00:15:09,175 --> 00:15:11,235
Oh, he's the, um,
the new officer?

332
00:15:11,310 --> 00:15:13,302
Yep. I think
he'll settle in all right.

333
00:15:13,379 --> 00:15:14,312
Mm-hmm.

334
00:15:14,380 --> 00:15:16,110
Prisoner 435, Jack Bulmer,

335
00:15:16,182 --> 00:15:18,515
has complained
that he has lost phone cards,

336
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,246
two one-ounce packets
of tobacco,

337
00:15:20,319 --> 00:15:22,413
a Game Boy, four games,

338
00:15:22,488 --> 00:15:25,822
a Sony Walkman, and some tapes.

339
00:15:25,892 --> 00:15:27,485
I also got a good informant
on the wing.

340
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,071
He seems to think
something's coming in.

341
00:15:29,095 --> 00:15:31,860
Like what?
Dixons opening a branch?

342
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,108
Anyway, I put it in my report.

343
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:35,260
Lad sometime makes stuff up.

344
00:15:35,334 --> 00:15:37,803
Mr. Marshall coming back, is he?

345
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:40,271
I've not been informed by HQ.

346
00:15:40,339 --> 00:15:43,832
But then, I wasn't privy
to the press release

347
00:15:43,910 --> 00:15:46,709
about the refurbishment costs
either.

348
00:15:46,779 --> 00:15:49,339
Is that true? They're gonna
spend 60 million on this place?

349
00:15:49,415 --> 00:15:51,441
I really have no idea.

350
00:15:51,517 --> 00:15:52,951
It was in <i>The Independent.</i>

351
00:15:53,019 --> 00:15:54,530
We recorded
the breakfast show in the club.

352
00:15:54,554 --> 00:15:56,580
I bet you did, Mr. Morgan.

353
00:15:56,656 --> 00:15:58,818
I had five phone cards.

354
00:15:58,891 --> 00:16:00,621
And Mark, next pad,

355
00:16:00,693 --> 00:16:03,219
he asked me if he can borrow
one of my phone cards.

356
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:05,307
I tell him no because I know
he won't pay me for it.

357
00:16:05,331 --> 00:16:06,890
Right?

358
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:09,458
I come back from association
last night,

359
00:16:09,535 --> 00:16:11,504
and my pad's been cleaned out.

360
00:16:11,571 --> 00:16:14,006
And this morning, on exercise,

361
00:16:14,073 --> 00:16:16,838
I heard a rumor
that somebody in D Wing

362
00:16:16,909 --> 00:16:18,241
has been offered one,

363
00:16:18,311 --> 00:16:21,440
and someone in this
wing's been offered one too.

364
00:16:21,514 --> 00:16:23,506
It's really got me down,
Miss Hewitt.

365
00:16:23,583 --> 00:16:26,576
I mean, that Game Boy's worth
at least 15 phone cards.

366
00:16:26,652 --> 00:16:28,450
All right, Jack.
I'll see what I can do.

367
00:16:28,521 --> 00:16:30,456
But you know it's against
prison regulations

368
00:16:30,523 --> 00:16:32,389
to do these trade-offs.

369
00:16:32,458 --> 00:16:34,324
Okay?

370
00:16:34,393 --> 00:16:35,656
[Sighs]

371
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:38,254
Now, Webster.

372
00:16:38,331 --> 00:16:40,891
You've made him
a 4:00 p.m. dental appointment.

373
00:16:40,967 --> 00:16:41,900
MORGAN: That's right.

374
00:16:41,968 --> 00:16:43,561
- Morning, Gov.
- Morning.

375
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,069
- Morning, Gov.
- Uh, morning.

376
00:16:45,137 --> 00:16:47,129
What time's Dr. Thomas due?

377
00:16:47,206 --> 00:16:50,734
2:00.
But Webster needs a dentist.

378
00:16:50,810 --> 00:16:53,050
I think we should have a new
arrangement with the doctor.

379
00:16:53,079 --> 00:16:54,389
I mean, as things
stand at the moment,

380
00:16:54,413 --> 00:16:56,813
if the inmates want to see him,
they have to wait until 2:00.

381
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:57,578
So?

382
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:59,209
It clashes
with their visiting times.

383
00:16:59,285 --> 00:17:01,263
If they have to see the doc,
then they miss their visit,

384
00:17:01,287 --> 00:17:03,586
and they won't miss their visit.

385
00:17:03,656 --> 00:17:06,421
Okay. Point taken.
Thank you.

386
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:11,559
I'd like to see Mr. Andrews
as soon as possible, please.

387
00:17:11,631 --> 00:17:12,826
WOMAN:
Can I take a message?

388
00:17:12,899 --> 00:17:14,343
No, I'd like to
speak to him personally.

389
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:17,235
- I'll check his diary.
- Thank you.

390
00:17:17,303 --> 00:17:18,303
Dr. Thomas is here.

391
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:19,839
Oh, good.
Show him in.

392
00:17:19,906 --> 00:17:22,899
Oh, and Mavis, was there
anything from the press office?

393
00:17:24,677 --> 00:17:26,397
- It's the governor.
- ANDREWS: Miss Hewitt.

394
00:17:26,445 --> 00:17:29,711
I'd like you to use the inserts
on the cuffs for Webster.

395
00:17:29,782 --> 00:17:31,910
Uh, let me check.

396
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:35,921
- Who?
- Howard Webster, Prisoner 533.

397
00:17:35,988 --> 00:17:38,014
He has a dental appointment
this afternoon.

398
00:17:38,090 --> 00:17:39,991
- Secure?
- Yes, secure.

399
00:17:40,059 --> 00:17:42,051
Well, he's already
absconded twice, so...

400
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:43,391
Thank you.

401
00:17:48,334 --> 00:17:52,135
Dr. Thomas,
I told you she's waiting.

402
00:17:52,204 --> 00:17:53,763
See you in a minute.

403
00:17:55,708 --> 00:17:58,371
Don't get involved.
He's got a shocking reputation.

404
00:17:58,444 --> 00:18:00,743
- As what?
- A ladies man.

405
00:18:00,813 --> 00:18:02,782
Belongs to the same golf club
as me husband.

406
00:18:02,848 --> 00:18:05,215
Different one every weekend,
and not golfing partners.

407
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:07,753
Did we get a fax from a HQ?

408
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:09,413
Well, I do have
quite a busy practice,

409
00:18:09,488 --> 00:18:13,255
but there's four of us,
so yeah, I should be able to.

410
00:18:13,326 --> 00:18:14,259
HEWITT: Good.

411
00:18:14,327 --> 00:18:16,038
It's just that if the men
have an appointment

412
00:18:16,062 --> 00:18:17,272
at the same time as their visit,

413
00:18:17,296 --> 00:18:18,740
then either
they don't get their visit

414
00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:20,232
or they don't
get their appointment.

415
00:18:20,299 --> 00:18:22,044
DR. THOMAS: Yeah, yeah.
You can leave it with me.

416
00:18:22,068 --> 00:18:23,468
- [Knocks]
- HEWITT: Thanks.

417
00:18:23,536 --> 00:18:24,970
I thought I put it on your desk.

418
00:18:25,037 --> 00:18:28,906
It's only the press release from
the article in <i>The Independent.</i>

419
00:18:31,777 --> 00:18:33,507
Could you give me two minutes?

420
00:18:33,579 --> 00:18:36,014
Uh, actually, I'm sorry,
I can't.

421
00:18:36,082 --> 00:18:37,015
I should go on my duty.

422
00:18:37,083 --> 00:18:38,642
Oh, well, don't let me detain.

423
00:18:38,718 --> 00:18:41,984
Okay. And I'll sort out
those duty periods.

424
00:18:42,054 --> 00:18:45,821
It was faxed in late, and, um,
we had the 6:00 TV call.

425
00:18:45,891 --> 00:18:48,087
I mean, you couldn't have
seen it anyway.

426
00:18:51,330 --> 00:18:55,324
In future, Mavis, anything
that comes in for me from HQ,

427
00:18:55,401 --> 00:18:57,996
anything at all,
you get it to me.

428
00:18:59,038 --> 00:19:02,702
I looked a total prat
this morning.

429
00:19:03,743 --> 00:19:05,268
Sorry.

430
00:19:07,847 --> 00:19:11,375
It's headquarters,
Mr. Andrews' secretary.

431
00:19:11,450 --> 00:19:13,817
Are you free for dinner?

432
00:19:13,886 --> 00:19:15,787
No, I'm sorry.

433
00:19:15,855 --> 00:19:17,949
But I didn't say which night?

434
00:19:18,024 --> 00:19:22,052
How about Tuesday or Thursday?

435
00:19:22,128 --> 00:19:25,223
No.
Now excuse me.

436
00:19:25,297 --> 00:19:27,459
Well, Saturday night, then?

437
